<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>Students may notice:</p>
<ul>
      <li>There are 6 groups of 3 in both diagrams.</li>
      <li>There are 15 black dots and 3 blue dots in each diagram.</li>
      <li>There are 18 dots in both diagrams.</li>
      <li>The first image and the array each have a group of dots that's a different color.</li>
    </ul>
<p>Students may wonder:</p>
<ul>
      <li>Why are some dots a different color?</li>
      <li>What situations could these diagrams represent?</li>
      <li>Why are the dots arranged differently in the 2 images?</li>
    </ul>
  </solution>


